Last Broadcast Date: Thu 6 Jan 2011
Joseph Gatyoung Khan As the people of southern Sudan prepare to vote in a referendum on independence, former Lost Boy Joseph Gatyoung Khan tells of his terrifying journey through the war-torn country and his emotional reunion with his parents 22 years later. Rescuing Haiti's children Nicole Dieudonne has devoted her life to saving children who have been abandoned and orphaned in Haiti. For Outlook, Mike Thomson visits the Christian Light Ministry orphanage in Port au Prince to meet Nicole and the children she has given a home to, some of whom were separated from their parents after last year's earthquake. Show less